
## ğŸ§­ **Navigation Commands**

```bash
cd /            # Go to root directory
cd /dev         # Enter the /dev directory
cd ..           # Go up one level
cd ~            # Go to the home directory
ls              # List contents of current directory
ls -l           # Long format listing
ls -i           # Show inode numbers
ls -li          # Long + inode
ls -l | grep ^b # Show block devices
ls -l | grep t$ # Show files ending with 't'
ls -l | grep sda # Filter for 'sda' devices
```

---

## ğŸ–¥ï¸ **Screen & Session Control**

```bash
clear           # Clear terminal screen
exit            # Exit terminal or shell
```

---

## ğŸ” **Process and System Info**

```bash
ps aux | grep 3922  # Search for process ID 3922
grep 3392           # Invalid, needs a file or pipe
```

---

## ğŸ§® **Word/Line Count with `wc`**

```bash
wc /etc/passwd        # Show lines, words, bytes
wc -l /etc/passwd     # Count lines only
wc -w /etc/passwd     # Count words
wc -c /etc/passwd     # Count characters
ls -l | wc -l         # Count number of listed files
ls -l | grep ^b | wc -l # Count block devices
wc -l                 # Waits for input unless piped
```

---

## ğŸ“„ **Viewing Files**

```bash
cat /etc/passwd       # Show full content
less /etc/passwd      # Scrollable view
more /etc/passwd      # Page-by-page view
head /etc/passwd      # First 10 lines
head -n 4 /etc/passwd # First 4 lines
tail /etc/passwd      # Last 10 lines
```

---

## ğŸ“ **File Creation and Sorting**

```bash
cat > File1           # Create and type into File1
cat File1             # Display contents
sort File1            # Sort lines
sort -r File1         # Sort in reverse order
sort -u File1         # Sort and remove duplicates
sort -u File1 > File2 # Save sorted unique lines into File2
cat File2             # Display File2
```

---

## ğŸ§ª **Editing Files with Vim & Vi**

```bash
vim File1             # Open File1 in Vim
vi File4              # Open File4 in Vi
cat > File4           # Create and type into File4
cat File4             # Display File4
```

---

## ğŸ”§ **Text Substitution using `sed`**

```bash
sed 's/Linux/Windows/1' File4  # Replace 1st occurrence
sed 's/Linux/Windows/2' File4  # Replace 2nd occurrence
sed 's/Linux/Windows/g' File4  # Replace all occurrences
```

---

## ğŸ” **Find Files and Attributes**

```bash
find /                 # List everything under root (slow)
find / -name File1     # Search for file by name
find / -inum 25179268  # Find file by inode number
find / -type b         # Find block devices
find / -size 10k       # Files exactly 10 KB
find / -size +10k      # Files larger than 10 KB
find / -user jaideep   # Files owned by user 'jaideep'
find / -group student  # Files belonging to group 'student'
```

â—ï¸Note:

* These have minor syntax issues:

  ```bash
  find /-user jaideep   # âŒ should be: find / -user jaideep
  find / f              # âŒ invalid
  ```

